    • write

      public org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFSheet write​(org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFSheet sheet)
      For each plant it writes new row in given sheet. Columns in each row order:
      1. ID given by ministry
      2. Number of permission
      3. Product name
      4. Producer name
      5. Chemical group
      6. URL of the product label
      7. Expiry date of the label
      8. End date of sale of the product
      9. End use date of the product
      10. Name and mass of active substance
      11. Toxicity standards for humans
      12. Toxicity standards for bees
      13. Toxicity standards for water environment
      14. Toxicity standards for environment
      15. Crops names
      16. Small area use
      17. Max dose value
      18. Dose unit
      19. Dose additional info
      20. Grace period
      21. Maximum number of uses per year
      22. Maximum number of uses per autumn
      23. Maximum number of uses per spring
      24. Additional information of treatments
      25. List of agrophags
      26. Markup to check information by hand
      27. Markup is this record to hide
      Specified by:
      write in interface XLSWriter
      Parameters:
      sheet - place to save new data
      Returns:
      updated sheet, filled with content
